   "source": [
    "# Model Setup: MedGemma
",
    "
",
    "## Goal
",
    "Authenticate with Hugging Face and load the MedGemma model.
",
    "
",
    "## Prerequisites
",
    "1.  **Hugging Face Account:** You need an account at [hf.co](https://hf.co).
",
    "2.  **Access Token:** Create a token at [hf.co/settings/tokens](https://hf.co/settings/tokens) with `read` permissions.
",
    "3.  **Model Access:** Visit [google/medgemma-1.5-4b-it](https://hf.co/google/medgemma-1.5-4b-it) and accept the license terms if required.
",
    "4.  **Environment Variables:** Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill in your `HF_TOKEN`.
",
    "
",
    "## Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os
",
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv
",
    "from huggingface_hub import login
",
    "import torch
",
    "from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoProcessor, AutoModelForVision2Seq
",
    "from PIL import Image
",
    "import requests
",
    "
",
    "# Load environment variables
",
    "load_dotenv()
",
    "
",
    "# Authenticate
",
    "hf_token = os.getenv('HF_TOKEN')
",
    "if hf_token:
",
    "    login(token=hf_token)
",
    "    print("Successfully logged in to Hugging Face.")
",
    "else:
",
    "    print("Warning: HF_TOKEN not found in .env file. Please set it or login manually.")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Load Model
",
    "We will load `google/medgemma-1.5-4b-it`. This is a multimodal model capable of processing images and text.
",
    "
",
    "**Note:** If you are running on a machine with limited RAM/VRAM, you might need to use 4-bit or 8-bit quantization. This requires `bitsandbytes`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model_id = "google/medgemma-1.5-4b-it"
",
    "
",
    "try:
",
    "    # Attempt to load processor and model
",
    "    # Using device_map="auto" to use GPU if available
",
    "    processor = AutoProcessor.from_pretrained(model_id)
",
    "    model = AutoModelForVision2Seq.from_pretrained(
",
    "        model_id, 
",
    "        device_map="auto", 
",
    "        torch_dtype=torch.float16,
",
    "        trust_remote_code=True # Often needed for newer/custom architectures
",
    "    )
",
    "    print(f"Successfully loaded {model_id}")
",
    "except Exception as e:
",
    "    print(f"Error loading model: {e}")
",
    "    print("Ensure you have accepted the model access terms on Hugging Face.")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Inference Example (Text Only)
",
    "Let's try a simple medical question."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "prompt = "What are the common symptoms of pneumonia?"
",
    "messages = [
",
    "    {"role": "user", "content": prompt}
",
    "]
",
    "
",
    "# Preprocess
",
    "# Note: Check exact chat template requirements for MedGemma. 
",
    "# Standard apply_chat_template might work if tokenizer supports it.
",
    "try:
",
    "    text = processor.tokenizer.apply_chat_template(messages, tokenize=False, add_generation_prompt=True)
",
    "except AttributeError:
",
    "    # Fallback if processor doesn't expose tokenizer directly in this way or template is missing
",
    "    text = f"User: {prompt}
Model:"
",
    "
",
    "inputs = processor(text=text, return_tensors="pt").to(model.device)
",
    "
",
    "# Generate
",
    "generated_ids = model.generate(**inputs, max_new_tokens=200)
",
    "generated_text = processor.batch_decode(generated_ids, skip_special_tokens=True)[0]
",
    "
",
    "print(generated_text)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
